{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.5",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 5 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:1",
      "text": "My son, attend to my wisdom, and incline thy ear to my prudence,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:2",
      "text": "That thou mayst keep thoughts, and thy lips may preserve instruction. Mind not the deceit of a woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:3",
      "text": "For the lips of a harlot are like a honeycomb dropping, and her throat is smoother than oil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:4",
      "text": "But her end is bitter as wormwood, and sharp as a two-edged sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:5",
      "text": "Her feet go down into death, and her steps go in as far as hell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:6",
      "text": "They walk not by the path of life, her steps are wandering, and unaccountable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:7",
      "text": "Now, therefore, my son, hear me, and depart not from the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:8",
      "text": "Remove thy way far from her, and come not nigh the doors of her house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:9",
      "text": "Give not thy honour to strangers, and thy years to the cruel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:10",
      "text": "Lest strangers be filled with thy strength, and thy labours be in another man's house,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:11",
      "text": "And thou mourn at the last, when thou shalt have spent thy flesh and thy body, and say;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:12",
      "text": "Why have I hated instruction, and my heart consented not to reproof,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:13",
      "text": "And have not heard the voice of them that taught me, and have not inclined my ear to masters?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:14",
      "text": "I have almost been in all evil, in the midst of the church and of the congregation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:15",
      "text": "Drink water out of thy own cistern, and the streams of thy own well:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:16",
      "text": "Let thy fountains be conveyed abroad, and in the streets divide thy waters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:17",
      "text": "Keep them to thyself alone, neither let strangers be partakers with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:18",
      "text": "Let thy vein be blessed, and rejoice with the wife of thy youth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:19",
      "text": "Let her be thy dearest hind, and most agreeable fawn: let her breasts inebriate thee at all times: be thou delighted continually with her love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:20",
      "text": "Why art thou seduced, my son, by a strange woman, and art cherished in the bosom of another?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:21",
      "text": "The Lord beholdeth the ways of man, and considereth all his steps.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:22",
      "text": "His own iniquities catch the wicked, and he is fast bound with the ropes of his own sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.5.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:23",
      "text": "He shall die, because he hath not received instruction, and in the multitude of his folly he shall be deceived.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
